"title": "6691: mercy, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6691: mercy, human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Believers are urged to show the same qualities of mercy and compassion towards one another as God demonstrates to them. A lack of mercy is regarded as characteristic of godless people.</p>\n<h2>The need for human mercy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:23\">PRO 18:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:49-Deut28:50\">DEU 28:49–28:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:6\">2SA 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:26\">1KI 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:21\">JOB 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:10\">PRO 21:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:6\">ISA 47:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9-Zech7:11\">ZEC 7:9–7:11</a></p>\n<h2>Believers should be merciful</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:8\">MIC 6:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:7\">MAT 5:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:36\">LUK 6:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9\">ZEC 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:12-Jas2:13\">JAS 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:9\">1PE 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:22\">JUD 1:22</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of mercy characterises the godless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:18\">ISA 13:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:23\">JER 6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:7\">JER 21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:42\">JER 50:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:11-Amos1:12\">AMO 1:11–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13-Hab1:17\">HAB 1:13–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of mercy on Israel's part was sometimes obedience to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:2\">DEU 7:2</a></strong> <em>Concerning the peoples they were to displace in the promised land.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:6-Deut13:9\">DEU 13:6–13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:11-Deut19:13\">DEU 19:11–19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:21\">DEU 19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:53-Deut28:54\">DEU 28:53–28:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:17-Josh6:19\">JOS 6:17–6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:18-1Sam15:19\">1SA 15:18–15:19</a></p>\n<h2>Mercy as a greeting and a blessing</h2>\n<h3>As a greeting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:2\">1TI 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:2\">2TI 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:3\">2JN 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:2\">JUD 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>As a blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:16\">GAL 6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:16-2Tim1:18\">2TI 1:16–1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:21\">JUD 1:21</a></p>",
